So, why Anaconda?

4
00:00:06.09 --> 00:00:09.03
Anaconda comes with a lot of packages

5
00:00:09.03 --> 00:00:11.04
that you need for data science.

6
00:00:11.04 --> 00:00:14.09
We will also use Conda, a package manager.

7
00:00:14.09 --> 00:00:17.07
Anaconda simplifies many of the challenges

8
00:00:17.07 --> 00:00:19.03
that a lot of people who are not

9
00:00:19.03 --> 00:00:22.05
full-time software
developers might run into.

10
00:00:22.05 --> 00:00:23.09
These are things like installing

11
00:00:23.09 --> 00:00:27.05
different versions of Python,
not having correct privileges,

12
00:00:27.05 --> 00:00:30.00
or not having the required packages.

13
00:00:30.00 --> 00:00:31.09
If you currently already have a version of

14
00:00:31.09 --> 00:00:33.07
pip or Conda installed,

15
00:00:33.07 --> 00:00:36.03
then you don't need to
reinstall everything.

16
00:00:36.03 --> 00:00:38.07
Just check that you have the five packages

17
00:00:38.07 --> 00:00:41.04
that we'll be using for
the course installed.

18
00:00:41.04 --> 00:00:45.05
These are NumPy, pandas, matplotlib,

19
00:00:45.05 --> 00:00:47.09
Seaborn, and Jupyter.

20
00:00:47.09 --> 00:00:50.08
If you have pip, type pip
install and the package name,

21
00:00:50.08 --> 00:00:54.08
so for example pip install
pandas for the pandas package.

22
00:00:54.08 --> 00:00:58.06
If you have Conda, type Conda
install and the package name.

23
00:00:58.06 --> 00:01:02.09
So, Conda install matplotlib
for the matplotlib package.

24
00:01:02.09 --> 00:01:06.01
We will use Python 3.6.

25
00:01:06.01 --> 00:01:08.04
Let's say you already have
another version of Python,

26
00:01:08.04 --> 00:01:11.07
say 2.7, and you are already working

27
00:01:11.07 --> 00:01:13.04
with some other packages there.

28
00:01:13.04 --> 00:01:15.01
Then you might want to create a separate

29
00:01:15.01 --> 00:01:17.07
virtual environment for this course.

30
